name: sqladmin
title: Cloud SQL Administration API
description: Creates and configures Cloud SQL instances, which provide fully-managed MySQL databases.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesImport.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesResetSslConfig.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation. All ssl client certificates will be deleted and a new server certificate will be created. Does not take effect until the next instance restart.

schemas.name: InstancesSetRootPasswordResponse
schemas.desc: Database instance set root password response.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesSetRootPassword.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: replicationType
fields.desc: The type of replication this instance uses. This can be either ASYNCHRONOUS or SYNCHRONOUS.

fields.name: settingsVersion
fields.desc: The version of instance settings. This is a required field for update method to make sure concurrent updates are handled properly. During update, use the most recent settingsVersion value for this instance and do not try to update this value.

fields.name: activationPolicy
fields.desc:
The activation policy for this instance. This specifies when the instance should be activated and is applicable only when the instance state is RUNNABLE. This can be one of the following.
ALWAYS: The instance should always be active.
NEVER: The instance should never be activated.
ON_DEMAND: The instance is activated upon receiving requests.

fields.name: authorizedGaeApplications
fields.desc: The App Engine app IDs that can access this instance.

fields.name: databaseReplicationEnabled
fields.desc: Configuration specific to read replica instance. Indicates whether replication is enabled or not.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#settings.

fields.name: locationPreference
fields.desc: The location preference settings. This allows the instance to be located as near as possible to either an App Engine app or GCE zone for better performance.

fields.name: pricingPlan
fields.desc: The pricing plan for this instance. This can be either PER_USE or PACKAGE.

fields.name: tier
fields.desc: The tier of service for this instance, for example D1, D2. For more information, see pricing.

fields.name: backupConfiguration
fields.desc: The daily backup configuration for the instance.

fields.name: databaseFlags
fields.desc: The database flags passed to the instance at startup.

fields.name: ipConfiguration
fields.desc: The settings for IP Management. This allows to enable or disable the instance IP and manage which external networks can connect to the instance.

fields.name: clientCert
fields.desc: The new client certificate and private key. The new certificate will not work until the instance is restarted.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCertsInsert.

fields.name: serverCaCert
fields.desc: The server Certificate Authority's certificate. If this is missing you can force a new one to be generated by calling resetSslConfig method on instances resource..

schemas.name: Tier
schemas.desc: A Google Cloud SQL service tier resource.

fields.name: DiskQuota
fields.desc: The maximum disk size of this tier in bytes.

fields.name: RAM
fields.desc: The maximum RAM usage of this tier in bytes.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#tier.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: The applicable regions for this tier.

fields.name: tier
fields.desc: An identifier for the service tier, for example D1, D2 etc. For related information, see Pricing.

fields.name: binLogCoordinates
fields.desc: Binary log coordinates, if specified, indentify the position up to which the source instance should be cloned. If not specified, the source instance is cloned up to the most recent binary log coordinates.

fields.name: destinationInstanceName
fields.desc: Name of the Cloud SQL instance to be created as a clone.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#cloneContext.

fields.name: sourceInstanceName
fields.desc: Name of the Cloud SQL instance to be cloned.

fields.name: database
fields.desc: The database (for example, guestbook) to which the import is made. If not set, it is assumed that the database is specified in the file to be imported.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#importContext.

fields.name: uri
fields.desc: A path to the MySQL dump file in Google Cloud Storage from which the import is made. The URI is in the form gs://bucketName/fileName. Compressed gzip files (.gz) are also supported.

fields.name: exportContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the export operation.

fields.name: ipAddress
fields.desc: The IP address assigned.

fields.name: timeToRetire
fields.desc: The due time for this IP to be retired in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z. This field is only available when the IP is scheduled to be retired.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of operation resources.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operationsList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

schemas.desc: Database instance set root password context.

fields.name: password
fields.desc: The password for the root user.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of tiers.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#tiersList.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of flags.

fields.name: kind

fields.desc: Contains details about the clone operation.

fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesClone.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An unique identifier for the operation associated with the cloned instance. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource, which has information about the operation.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesDelete.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: items

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

fields.name: commonName
fields.desc: User supplied name. Must be a distinct name from the other certificates for this instance. New certificates will not be usable until the instance is restarted.

fields.name: enabled
fields.desc: Whether this configuration is enabled.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Identifier for this configuration. This gets generated automatically when a backup configuration is created.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupConfiguration.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: Start time for the daily backup configuration in UTC timezone in the 24 hour format - HH:MM.

fields.name: binaryLogEnabled
fields.desc: Whether binary log is enabled. If backup configuration is disabled, binary log must be disabled as well.

fields.name: table
fields.desc: Tables to export, or that were exported, from the specified database. If you specify tables, specify one and only one database.

fields.name: uri
fields.desc: The path to the file in Google Cloud Storage where the export will be stored, or where it was already stored. The URI is in the form gs://bucketName/fileName. If the file already exists, the operation fails. If the filename ends with .gz, the contents are compressed.

fields.name: database
fields.desc: Databases (for example, guestbook) from which the export is made. If unspecified, all databases are exported.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#exportContext.

fields.name: importContext
fields.desc: Contains details about the import operation.

fields.name: authorizedNetworks
fields.desc: The list of external networks that are allowed to connect to the instance using the IP. In CIDR notation, also known as 'slash' notation (e.g. 192.168.100.0/24).

fields.name: enabled
fields.desc: Whether the instance should be assigned an IP address or not.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#ipConfiguration.

fields.name: requireSsl
fields.desc: Whether the mysqld should default to 'REQUIRE X509' for users connecting over IP.

schemas.name: Flag
schemas.desc: A Google Cloud SQL service flag resource.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the flag. Flags are typed to being BOOLEAN, STRING, INTEGER or NONE. NONE is used for flags which do not take a value, such as skip_grant_tables.

fields.name: allowedStringValues
fields.desc: For STRING flags, a list of strings that the value can be set to.

fields.name: appliesTo
fields.desc: The database version this flag applies to. Currently this can only be [MYSQL_5_5].

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#flag.

fields.name: maxValue
fields.desc: For INTEGER flags, the maximum allowed value.

fields.name: minValue
fields.desc: For INTEGER flags, the minimum allowed value.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: This is the name of the flag. Flag names always use underscores, not hyphens, e.g. max_allowed_packet

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesExport.

fields.name: operation

schemas.name: BackupRun
schemas.desc: A database instance backup run resource.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time the backup operation completed in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the database instance.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time the backup operation actually started in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: backupConfiguration
fields.desc: Backup Configuration identifier.

fields.name: dueTime
fields.desc: The due time of this run in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: enqueuedTime
fields.desc: The time the run was enqueued in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: error
fields.desc: Information about why the backup operation failed. This is only present if the run has the FAILED status.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupRun.

fields.name: status
fields.desc: The status of this run.

schemas.name: InstanceOperation
schemas.desc: An Operations resource contains information about database instance operations such as create, delete, and restart. Operations resources are created in response to operations that were initiated; you never create them directly.

fields.name: userEmailAddress
fields.desc: The email address of the user who initiated this operation.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: The time this operation finished in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instanceOperation.

fields.name: operationType
fields.desc: The type of the operation. Valid values are CREATE, DELETE, UPDATE, RESTART, IMPORT, EXPORT, BACKUP_VOLUME, RESTORE_VOLUME.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: The time this operation actually started in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: state
fields.desc: The state of an operation. Valid values are PENDING, RUNNING, DONE, UNKNOWN.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: enqueuedTime
fields.desc: The time this operation was enqueued in UTC timezone in RFC 3339 format, for example 2012-11-15T16:19:00.094Z.

fields.name: error
fields.desc: The error(s) encountered by this operation. Only set if the operation results in an error.

fields.name: exportContext
fields.desc: The context for export operation, if applicable.

fields.name: importContext
fields.desc: The context for import operation, if applicable.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the database instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesInsert.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

fields.name: certSerialNumber
fields.desc: Serial number, as extracted from the certificate.

fields.name: commonName
fields.desc: User supplied name. Constrained to [a-zA-Z.-_ ]+.

fields.name: createTime
fields.desc: Time when the certificate was created.

fields.name: expirationTime
fields.desc: Time when the certificate expires.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the database instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCert.

fields.name: sha1Fingerprint
fields.desc: Sha1 Fingerprint.

fields.name: cert
fields.desc: PEM representation.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of client certificates for the instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#sslCertsList.

fields.name: maxDiskSize
fields.desc: The maximum disk size of the instance in bytes.

fields.name: region
fields.desc: The geographical region. Can be us-central, asia-east1 or europe-west1. Defaults to us-central. The region can not be changed after instance creation.

fields.name: serverCaCert
fields.desc: SSL configuration.

fields.name: settings
fields.desc: The user settings.

fields.name: instanceType
fields.desc:
The instance type. This can be one of the following.
CLOUD_SQL_INSTANCE: Regular Cloud SQL instance.
READ_REPLICA_INSTANCE: Cloud SQL instance acting as a read-replica.

fields.name: ipAddresses
fields.desc: The assigned IP addresses for the instance.

fields.name: replicaNames
fields.desc: The replicas of the instance.

fields.name: state
fields.desc:
The current serving state of the Cloud SQL instance. This can be one of the following.
RUNNABLE: The instance is running, or is ready to run when accessed.
SUSPENDED: The instance is not available, for example due to problems with billing.
PENDING_CREATE: The instance is being created.
MAINTENANCE: The instance is down for maintenance.
UNKNOWN_STATE: The state of the instance is unknown.

fields.name: currentDiskSize
fields.desc: The current disk usage of the instance in bytes.

fields.name: project
fields.desc: The project ID of the project containing the Cloud SQL instance. The Google apps domain is prefixed if applicable.

fields.name: instance
fields.desc: Name of the Cloud SQL instance. This does not include the project ID.

fields.name: serviceAccountEmailAddress
fields.desc: The service account email address assigned to the instance.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the resource.

fields.name: ipv6Address
fields.desc: The IPv6 address assigned to the instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instance.

fields.name: masterInstanceName
fields.desc: The name of the instance which will act as master in the replication setup.

fields.name: connectionName
fields.desc: Connection name of the Cloud SQL instance used in connection strings.

fields.name: databaseVersion
fields.desc: The database engine type and version. Can be MYSQL_5_5 or MYSQL_5_6. Defaults to MYSQL_5_5. The databaseVersion cannot be changed after instance creation.

schemas.name: InstanceSetRootPasswordRequest
schemas.desc: Database instance set root password request.

fields.name: setRootPasswordContext
fields.desc: Set Root Password Context.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#instancesRestoreBackup.

fields.name: operation
fields.desc: An identifier that uniquely identifies the operation. You can use this identifier to retrieve the Operations resource that has information about the operation.

schemas.name: LocationPreference
schemas.desc: Preferred location. This specifies where a Cloud SQL instance should preferably be located, either in a specific Compute Engine zone, or co-located with an App Engine application. Note that if the preferred location is not available, the instance will be located as close as possible within the region. Only one location may be specified.

fields.name: followGaeApplication
fields.desc: The App Engine application to follow, it must be in the same region as the Cloud SQL instance.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#locationPreference.

fields.name: zone
fields.desc: The preferred Compute Engine zone (e.g. us-centra1-a, us-central1-b, etc.).

fields.name: items
fields.desc: A list of backup runs in reverse chronological order of the enqueued time.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#backupRunsList.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

fields.name: binLogFileName
fields.desc: Name of the binary log file for a Cloud SQL instance.

fields.name: binLogPosition
fields.desc: Position (offset) within the binary log file.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#binLogCoordinates.

fields.name: certInfo
fields.desc: The public information about the cert.

fields.name: certPrivateKey
fields.desc: The private key for the client cert, in pem format. Keep private in order to protect your security.

schemas.name: DatabaseFlags
schemas.desc: MySQL flags for Cloud SQL instances.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the flag. These flags are passed at instance startup, so include both MySQL server options and MySQL system variables. Flags should be specified with underscores, not hyphens. For more information, see Configuring MySQL Flags in the Google Cloud SQL documentation, as well as the official MySQL documentation for server options and system variables.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value of the flag. Booleans should be set to on for true and off for false. This field must be omitted if the flag doesn't take a value.

fields.name: code
fields.desc: Identifies the specific error that occurred.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This is always sql#operationError.
